# rinnegan bundled Caddy config: self-signed HTTPS reverse proxy.
#
# Terminates TLS on :8443 (all interfaces, 0.0.0.0/::) with Caddy's internal
# CA and proxies to the rinnegan server on localhost:8442. The certificate is
# self-signed, so browsers show a one-time warning that the user accepts --
# rinnegan does NOT install the CA into any trust store (skip_install_trust),
# so no NSS/Java/system store is touched and Caddy never shells out to sudo.
#
# The site is addressed with two names so it works no matter how a client
# connects. `https://localhost:8443` gives `tls internal` a subject, so a leaf
# cert for `localhost` is minted up front (a bare `:8443` site would leave the
# internal CA with nothing to sign and no cert would ever be served). The
# host-less `https://:8443` matches ANY Host header -- including IP literals
# such as 127.0.0.1 (the connection the CI smoke test makes) or the machine's
# LAN IP -- so those requests still route to the reverse proxy. `bind 0.0.0.0 ::`
# binds every interface, and `default_sni localhost` makes connections that
# send no SNI (any IP-literal client) get served the localhost cert.
#
# `rinnegan serve --https` sets XDG_DATA_HOME / XDG_CONFIG_HOME to
# <bundle>/caddy-data, so the local CA and issued certs stay inside the
# bundle directory. Delete caddy-data/ to regenerate the CA.
{
	admin off
	auto_https disable_redirects
	skip_install_trust
	default_sni localhost
}

https://localhost:8443, https://:8443 {
	bind 0.0.0.0 ::
	tls internal
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8442
}
